intro: Rhynchospora spiciformis f. setacea, commonly known as the dense-flowered spike-rush, is a flowering plant belonging to the Cyperaceae family. It is characterized by its dense, spike-like inflorescence and narrow, grass-like leaves. The plant typically grows in wet or marshy habitats, often in temperate regions. Its flowers are usually small and inconspicuous, with three stamens and a single pistil. This fern-like rush is often found in wetlands and is an important component of the aquatic plant community.
